LOCUS       PuroR                    199 aa                     UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  PuroR is the Streptomyces alboniger puromycin N-acetyltransferase
            (PAC), a 199-aa GNAT-family enzyme that inactivates puromycin by
            N-acetylation and serves as a dominant selectable marker..
